text: Kamet is a mountain in the Himalayas range, in India. It is the 29th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Frank Smythe, Eric Shipton, R.L. Holdsworth, and Lewa Sherpa, in 1931. ==References== Category:Himalayas Category:Mountains of India Category:Uttarakhand
title: Kamet
